Troubleshooting Tips
OpenCanary won't start:

Check if ports are already in use: sudo netstat -tulpn | grep <port>
Verify configuration file syntax (valid JSON)
Check log file permissions: ls -l ~/opencanary-logs/
No alerts appearing:

Verify OpenCanary is running: ps aux | grep opencanary
Check firewall rules: sudo iptables -L
Generate test traffic from different terminal
Database errors:

Ensure SQLite3 is installed: sudo apt install sqlite3
Check file permissions on database file
Delete and reinitialize database if corrupted
